dN8SmhCYLdU.title: 15 Min Mobility Class

mpe5U2fto8s.title: Registration is OPEN for Intention Factor® Programming!
mpe5U2fto8s.description:
In this vid, I'm quickly explaining the four different tracks I offer in my Intention Factor® Programming (see below). Programming is subscription based, charged every six weeks at $44.99 and registration closes on July 9th at 11:59pm EST. Join here: https://intentionfactor.com/memberships-online-classes

Posture - Best place to go to set a solid foundation, this programming focuses on posterior chain strength, core integration (with pelvic floor education) and mindfulness/postural awareness. You'll also learn how to assess your own posture! Ideal for people who are either brand new to working out, or people who have worked out for ages but keep finding themselves continually injured.

Glute: Ideal for people needing a complement to their current workouts, or for someone who has "graduated" from the Posture Program, or for someone who is solely interested in aesthetics and looking for glute gains.

Fitness: This is a comprehensive workout program that includes cardio as well. Best for people who know their way around a gym and who are currently pain free, and who have either plateaued in their training, are bored, or just want a plan, and don't want to have to think about it.

Working out with your Cycle: For people with regular cycles (it's beyond my scope of practice to help you re-gain your cycle, or help balance hormones - that's the job of a dr), and who want to optimize their training around their cycle. You'll get a high level overview of the four different phases of a cycle, figure out where you are in your cycle, and choose workouts tailored to the cycle you're in. 

Join now: https://intentionfactor.com/memberships-online-classes

LaOASR0n3S8.title: Two Moves to Help Rotator Cuff and Upper Back
LaOASR0n3S8.description:
Here are two moves to help strengthen the rotator cuff muscles and upper back muscles for improved shoulder positioning and posture. In the video, I'm using the yellow band from this set: https://amzn.to/3FHmDml. 

If you're interested in my new continuing ed posture course for yoga teachers (or anyone!), you can check it out here: https://intentionfactor.com/memberships-online-classes. It's a four part workshop series via zoom where I'll teach you how I assess posture from the front, side and back, and then you'll learn stretching and strengthening techniques to improve upon the posture you're seeing, and I'll explain how to integrate these moves into your yoga class design and sequencing.

e-NL6pBis_E.title: 27 Minute Bosu and Resistance Band Total Body Workout
e-NL6pBis_E.description:
We'll start with a banded clam to activate glute medius, and then move into a single leg glute bridge (you really don't need the Bosu pod to do this, you could do it on the ground), and then we have some head tap push ups with a twist - great for upper body strength and rotation through the spine, and a great side plank with leg tap which will activate the core and adductors and upper body as well. Hope you enjoy!

oRoAVYT9odQ.title: Intentional Summer Mantra Box® Unveiling
oRoAVYT9odQ.description:
It's that time of year again! Time to unveil our latest Mantra Box®: Intentional Summer. Inspired by my hiking trip to Peru where I hiked the Salkantay Trek (you can read about it here: https://www.yogabycandace.com/blog/2021/7/11/my-experience-hiking-the-salkantay-trek-to-machu-picchu), I wanted to fill this quarter's Mantra Box® with items to help inspire you to get outside, have adventure, and do something that brings you joy. 

You can check out the blog post here with all the details:
Or if you're ready to order now, you can do so here: https://www.yogabycandace.com/ybc-mantra-box/intentional-summer-mantra-box

All the details: 
OrganiLip (https://www.organilip.com/) - $4 - @organilip - OrganiLip ultra-rich lip balm is infused with 100% pure organic Sea Buckthorn berry oil to moisturize and rejuvenate the most delicate skin on your body. Blended with soothing calendula and nourishing organic coconut oil, OrganiLip is made from only pure, organic ingredients that are fair trade certified. Their products never contain petroleum or palm oil and are 100% cruelty free.

Crushed Tonic (https://www.crushedtonic.com/collections/crushed-tonic/products/sampler) - $7.50 - @crushedtonic - Crushed Tonic has designed a wonder-product for hair, skin and nails. You’ll get an Original Crush with marine collagen, biotin, probiotics and lucuma. This is perfect if you’re a coffee drinker. Just add the Original Crush right to your cup of joe. Hate coffee but still crave caffeine? You’ll also get the  Matcha Crush which has marine collagen, biotin, probiotics and match!

PlantFusion Complete Protein in Red Velvet (https://plantfusion.com/products/complete-plant-protein) - $4.99 - @plantfusion - There’s a reason why most protein shakes look and taste the same. Most of them are all made the same way, using the same ingredients. When PlantFusion was started, they made a choice to use better ingredients like yellow peas from northern hills of France and better flavors like vanilla bean from Madagascar. It turns out that these choices mattered because people noticed the difference. You’ll get two red velvet protein powders to help power you through outdoor adventure!

Scentuals Soap (https://www.scentuals.com/) - $4.38 - @scentuals - Handmade with a luxuriously soothing blend of peppermint, spearmint and nourishing Olive, Palm and Coconut oils, organic herbs and spices, this soap is a dream. This 100% natural soap creates a rich lather and gently cleanses while hydrating skin. Highly recommended for people with sensitive skin, eczema or psoriasis.

Plum Deluxe Tea (https://www.plumdeluxe.com/teashop) - $7 - @plumdeluxe - These teas give you the best reasons to slow down, to do whatever it is you’re going to do- whether that’s reading your favorite book, writing a piece of prose, a goofy happy dance in the kitchen with your favorite cuppa, or simply staring out of a window. Teas that are punctuated by flavor, aroma, and taste help with whatever moments are ahead of you and make them feel better than they ever did before you poured the tea. We love these!

Liquid IV (https://www.googleadservices.com/pagead/aclk) - $4.78 - @liquidiv - Hydration Multiplier is a great-tasting, Non-GMO electrolyte drink mix powered by Cellular Transport Technology (CTT®️ ) to deliver hydration to your bloodstream faster & more efficiently than water alone. These taste fantastic, and the best part? 1 Liquid I.V. can provide the same hydration as drinking 2-3 bottles of water & contains 3x the electrolytes of traditional sports drinks with 5 essential vitamins.

Organic Cotton X-Long Yoga Strap (https://cleveryoga.com/products/yoga-strap?_pos=1&_sid=a647c54fa&_ss=r) - $11.99 - @gocleveryoga - This organic cotton yoga strap has D rings for secure binding when needed, and is extra long, at ten feet! We love a good yoga strap for daily asana practice regardless of how long you’ve been practicing. It can help in restorative poses, balancing poses, and so much more!

Adventure Stickers - $8 - You’re getting 3 adventure themed stickers to help inspire your journaling, one of the best ways to reconnect with yourself and capture a memory beyond the snap of a photo. Use them to decorate the cover of your journal or an individual post!

Journals - $12 - Keep track of your adventures, mood, feelings, thoughts and ideas with this journal. The paper is excellent quality, and the journal is big enough to get all your ideas out on a page or two, but it’s small enough that you can throw in your backpack for hiking, or in your purse for a solo coffee shop visit. 

Jones Bar - $2.42 (https://jonesbar.com/collections/bars/products/banana-chocolate-chip) - The most delicious, real-foods bar you'll ever taste! I love them for their super simple, clean ingredients list and the taste that's outta this world. I took them to Peru with me to help me on the trek and they were wonderful!

IiZMe7ePxik.title: 17 Min Resistance Band Workout
IiZMe7ePxik.description:
Put on your favorite playlist and let's get to it i! Here's a 17 min resistance band workout - you'll just need a short loop and long loop resistance band. These are from Bosu which you can find right on their website. This workout will activate the glutes and hamstrings and psoas and quads with the first movement - a forward and backwards monster walk. Next up is a lat pullover - great for the back. The next move is a wall sit with hip abduction - again, great for glutes and hamstrings. Next up we have a face pull - great for upper back strength - if you're a sloucher, this is a good one!

cUZLYsNchdE.title: 17 Min Bosu Resistance Band Workout
cUZLYsNchdE.description:
Here's a 17 minute total body workout with a long loop resistance band, and a Bosu Balance Trainer (this is their sports version). This workout has four movements - the first one is a downward dog hamstring strengthening exercise. Downward dog push ups come next - great for strengthening the upper body. Following that we have a lateral step with hip abduction - excellent for balance, core and glute medius strengthening plus cardio. Lastly, we have a core movement with a funky dead bug exercise. As always, move within a pain-free range.

As always, work within a pain-free range and take breaks as needed. Hope you enjoy!

vWI13cjdKGA.title: 15 Min Total Body Foam Rolling Warm Up or Cool Down
vWI13cjdKGA.description:
A great way to warm up or cool down, this 15 minute guided foam rolling video should be a staple in your movement practice. I don't have a favorite foam roller, but I do prefer the high density ones (https://amzn.to/35S1ncJ) and some parts of the body, like the peroneals and calves, can be hard to get, so I like this stick (https://amzn.to/38VWzoR) for those areas. You're going to want to do a quick passthrough of your entire body, pausing for 30 seconds or so on any tender spots. If you don't have a tender spot, then just keep it moving! Foam rolling is great for circulation, and helping to release restricted muscles. Hope you enjoy!

hD6BNqwh7EQ.title: 45 Minute Total Body Strengthening and Relaxing Yoga Practice
hD6BNqwh7EQ.description:
This practice is brought to you by Bhoga - a great small business that makes incredible yoga mats and accessories based out of California. In this practice, I am using their Bhoga Infinity Blocks and their Lotus Sun Alignment Mat which you can check out here: https://bhoga.com/product/two-bhoga-blocks-plus-alignment-mat-super-saver-starter-pak/. You can use code YBC10 for 10% off (no minimum purchase), or YBC20 for 20% off orders over $99.


The Lotus-Sun Alignment Mat has excellent grip and is slip resistant, and made out of 100% natural rubber with an eco-polyurethane top skin. There are no PVC, silicone or phthalates, and it is eco-friendly and a super durable mat. The yoga mat is extra wide, long and thick with dimensions 26.75″ x 72″ x .2″. The mandala design is laser engraved and will not rub off. It comes with an all-cotton mat carrying strap. 

The Infinity Blocks are super ergonomic, super versatile and mold well to the body. 
They have two arched sides with rounded edges and two flat sides that can be moved and manipulated to fit your body's spinal curves, the arches of the hands, feet, you name it. 
They are made out of sustainable and renewable rubber-tree hardwood, and the dimensions are:
10 1/4 x 5 7/8 x 3 1/2″  (large) 6 3/4 x 3 1/2 x 3 1/2 “ (small)
2-2.5 lb each (large) 1- 1 1/4 lb each (small)


In today's practice we are going to move through a challenging strength building practice that also incorporates stretching and deep relaxation for the ultimate feel-good yoga practice. As always, work within a pain-free range.

fBep_cRWP-o.description:
I started Mantra Box® a few years ago with the intention to help support small businesses in the health and wellness world. Each quarter, we curate a box around a particular theme. This quarter's box is a Home Spa Edition, and within the box is a Mantra, a short phrase to help guide your intention for the quarter and to help you live more mindfully. You'll also receive a number of full size and trial products from small businesses you've likely never heard of. Each box will support at least four BIPOC business owners, and this one supports six - you can meet all of the business owners we've supported with this box here: https://www.yogabycandace.com/blog/2020/9/8/mantra-box-home-spa-edition

urvJaypKED8.title: Chill Out Restorative Yoga Practice to De-Stress
urvJaypKED8.description:
This video is sponsored by BodyChek Wellness (www.bodychekwellness.com). They have an incredible line of organic CBD products for humans and they *also* just came out with a Pet Formula that has been the only thing that helps my senior Siberian Husky with his thunderstorm anxiety! You can use code YBC25 for 25% off their entire line of products at BodyChekWellness.com.

This is a restorative yoga practice. You'll be in each pose for between 4 - 5 minutes, and you'll need a yoga bolster (This is the brand I'm using: https://amzn.to/2P0WQMx) but if you don't have a bolster you can use a couch cushion or body pillow! Try to melt and relax into each position - you want it to feel basically effortless. This style of yoga practice is excellent for de-stressing, calming the nervous system, and helping to open the fascia. Hope you enjoy!

ubYtKbqaiHI.title: Dead Bugs and Core Bracing
ubYtKbqaiHI.description:
If you're dealing with back pain, or you feel you need to improve your core strength, this is the video for you. A core brace is a great skill to know how to do because it'll help to protect your lumbar spine. This video will teach you how to core brace, then how to use that brace in the dead bug exercise. Following that, we go through a mini vinyasa to practice what it feels like to use the core brace in yoga asana, particularly in transitions. 

If you're interested, I offer custom 6week workout programs aimed to help people with their muscle imbalances: https://www.yogabycandace.com/workout-programs/pt-program

MVIXpPtajws.title: Improve Your Fallen Arches
MVIXpPtajws.description:
Yoga is awesome for a lot of things, but sometimes we need more than yoga to help us improve upon postural issues. Strength training and foam rolling, in additional to yoga, can be really helpful when it comes to improving fallen arches. This movement practice is meant for people who have fallen arches and toes pointing out to the side. This is likely impacting posture, and just like with yoga, it's help to start from the foundation, and when standing and walking, the foundation are our feet. To begin, we will use a foam roller to gently release the peroneals and IT band, and then we will work on a few movements to strengthen the adductors (inner thighs). If you're a total beginner, it's suggested to start with this video twice per week and work your way up to daily. The biggest piece to making a change is the mind-body awareness, so I discuss that throughout. Hope this is helpful!

nQSu39qu7B4.title: No Equipment Hiit Workout
nQSu39qu7B4.description:
In today's hiit class, we'll work the glutes, legs and core. As always, I liked to offer options so that people of all levels will be challenged. 

The first movement is an air squat, or you can make it more challenging by adding a jump. You'll load through the heels to activate your glutes and hamstrings, and be mindful that your chest stays upright. 

The next movement is a skater step and touchdown (or you can add a jump to make it more challenging). Try to keep the stepping foot pointed straight out in front of you rather than off to the side, and that'll work your adductors. Think about sending your hips back, rather than down and that'll work your glutes.

The last movement is for the core, and it'll work the rectus abdominis (6 pack part of the core). Beginners can keep their legs are little more lifted, while more advanced practitioners can extend their legs lower for more of a challenge. 

Have fun!!

XE9b3_4GdbI.title: 30 Min Baby Grasshopper and Crow Pose Jumpback Yoga Class
XE9b3_4GdbI.description:
This video is brought to you by 2nd Wind Health - they make awesome yoga products ranging from yoga mats to wheels, blocks and more. Check them out: https://2ndwindhealth.com/

In this 30 minute practice, we'll fire up the core strength, activate upper body strength, and work our way up to crow pose. Then, we'll play with initiating mind/muscle memory and come into crow pose jumpbacks. From there, we'll work our way up to baby grasshopper.

ifcFpVu6bNk.title: 30 Minute Vinyasa Practice
ifcFpVu6bNk.description:
This is the first half of a 60 minute vinyasa practice that is available for Premium Subscribers of our Namaslay® Studios Online Membership which you can join here: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCI9s9nFu2m3K2CvhO2QVfTg/join

As always, move in a pain-free range, and take breaks as needed. Vinyasa is a flow style of practice, so you'll link breath with movement, and it's a bit more athletic and faster paced than hatha, yin or restorative, which is much slower. Give it a try and let me know how it goes! 

Here's a link for a yoga cool down which will round this practice out: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=h60ZvwA8He0

6MAjEW8XQlc.title: 45 Minute Restorative and Yin Yoga Class with a Wheel
6MAjEW8XQlc.description:
Thrilled to partner up with 2nd Wind Health to bring you this 45 Minute Restorative and Yin Yoga Class with a Wheel. A Yoga Wheel can be a great prop to add to your yoga practice, as they bring a bit of movement, height, and a different twist to the practice. The yoga wheel I'm using in this video is made of cork, a material I absolutely love for yoga props because it has the perfect amount of give to it, which feels nice when you lay your body over it. You can check out the wheel here: https://2ndwindhealth.com/collections/yoga-wheels/products/lotus-cork-yoga-wheel.

In this video we'll do a bit of side body opening, back and chest opening, and then work our way into opening through the hips, thighs and hamstrings. Hope you enjoy!

CKVkkcgPYas.description:
This past year, I became an E-RYT500hr yoga teacher, and a  Certified Personal Trainer through the National Academy of Sports Medicine. I also opened up my brick and mortar boutique yoga and fitness studio called Namaslay® Studios in Ridgefield, CT. I wanted to start sharing more strategic content just like I do at the studio, and realized that YouTube now offers a membership option - so the Namaslay® Studios Online platform has been born! Here's everything you need to know: 

1) Nothing will change, if you don't want it to change. Not into being a member? No worries! I'll still be posting yoga and fitness content regularly. 

2) If you want to deepen your yoga practice, build strength and begin meditation, the membership option is for you! Each month, on the first of the month,  you will get exclusive yoga, fitness and meditation videos. You'll gain access through the 'Community Tab' on my channel, and you'll also be able to chat with me, add your requests for the following month, and more. I'm so excited about it! 

There are two levels: 

a) Namaslay® Basic, $9.99/mo
You'll get: 
-one 60 Min yoga video 
-one workshop video 
-one guided meditation practice

You'll get: 
-four 60 Min yoga videos (two will be more athletic/vinyasa/power based, one will be a hatha style, and one will be restorative or yin)

LnRDqrc04ns.title: Restorative Yoga Foundations: Part 4
LnRDqrc04ns.description:
This video is brought to you by Carolina Morning, who sent me their rectangular bolsters which make for perfect props in the restorative yoga practice. The bolsters feature an eco-friendly design sewn with organic cotton and stuffed with hypoallergenic kapok fiber. Their quality is fantastic. You can check them out here: https://zafu.net/yoga-bolster

This video is the fourth in our four part video series. 
Restorative Yoga Foundations, Pt 1: This video was an informational talk on restorative yoga - what it is, and what it isn't. 
Restorative Yoga Foundations, Pt 2: This video discussed how to calm the monkey mind, and how to sequence a restorative yoga practice. Then, we do a short practice together. 
Restorative Yoga Foundations, Pt 3: The video demonstrated ways we can use various yoga props to make the restorative yoga poses more accessible and more comfortable. Comfort is key for this style of yoga, so this video is really important.

In this last video, I share three unique restorative yoga poses that I don't typically see programmed into in-studio yoga classes. 

Hope you enjoyed this series! Please feel free to let me know in the comments section below if there's another series you'd like to see!

yRmzxfc_JRs.title: Restorative Yoga Foundations: Part3
yRmzxfc_JRs.description:
This video is generously brought to you by Carolina Morning, who provided the bolsters in the video. The bolsters feature an eco-friendly design sewn with organic cotton and stuffed with hypoallergenic kapok fiber. Their quality is fantastic. You can check them out here: https://zafu.net/yoga-bolster.

Welcome to part three of our four part series (Here's Part 1: https://www.yogabycandace.com/blog/2019/11/27/restorative-yoga-foundations-part-1 and Part 2: https://www.yogabycandace.com/blog/2019/12/9/restorative-yoga-foundations-part-2). 

The goal of this series was to help go a bit deeper into Restorative Yoga, which is a really calming, relaxing style of yoga that is perfect any time of year, but especially during the holiday season, which can be so stressful. Part one was a mostly informational session about Restorative Yoga - what it is, what to expect, and how it's different from yin and other types of yoga. Part two was about how to sequence a restorative yoga class, and a few key concepts to keep in mind. In Part Three, I'm sharing a few ways to manipulate the yoga props so that you (or your students) can feel much more comfortable in the poses. And that's key here - you always want to feel as comfortable as you can when it comes to restorative yoga, because the whole point is about letting go, relaxing into it, melting, and allowing the fascia to gently open up. Hope you enjoy! 

If you're interested in learning more about restorative yoga, consider coming to one of our yoga teacher training programs in 2020! More info: https://www.yogabycandace.com/yoga-workshops and https://www.yogabycandace.com/yoga-retreats-teacher-trainings

localized.title: Restorative Yoga Foundations: Part3
localized.description:
This video is generously brought to you by Carolina Morning, who provided the bolsters in the video. The bolsters feature an eco-friendly design sewn with organic cotton and stuffed with hypoallergenic kapok fiber. Their quality is fantastic. You can check them out here: https://zafu.net/yoga-bolster.

Welcome to part three of our four part series (Here's Part 1: https://www.yogabycandace.com/blog/2019/11/27/restorative-yoga-foundations-part-1 and Part 2: https://www.yogabycandace.com/blog/2019/12/9/restorative-yoga-foundations-part-2). 

The goal of this series was to help go a bit deeper into Restorative Yoga, which is a really calming, relaxing style of yoga that is perfect any time of year, but especially during the holiday season, which can be so stressful. Part one was a mostly informational session about Restorative Yoga - what it is, what to expect, and how it's different from yin and other types of yoga. Part two was about how to sequence a restorative yoga class, and a few key concepts to keep in mind. In Part Three, I'm sharing a few ways to manipulate the yoga props so that you (or your students) can feel much more comfortable in the poses. And that's key here - you always want to feel as comfortable as you can when it comes to restorative yoga, because the whole point is about letting go, relaxing into it, melting, and allowing the fascia to gently open up. Hope you enjoy! 

If you're interested in learning more about restorative yoga, consider coming to one of our yoga teacher training programs in 2020! More info: https://www.yogabycandace.com/yoga-workshops and https://www.yogabycandace.com/yoga-retreats-teacher-trainings

9IYUy6mWdf0.title: Restorative Yoga Foundations, Part 1
9IYUy6mWdf0.description:
This is the first video in a Four Part Restorative Yoga Foundations series brought to you by Carolina Mornings, who sent me the bolsters I'm using in the video which you can find here: https://zafu.net/product/bolster. This video is more of an introduction to restorative yoga, rather than an actual restorative yoga class, although we do two poses together towards the end just to experience what it feels like to practice restorative yoga. I also discuss the difference between restorative and yin yoga, different props to consider, what to expect if you go to a class, how to dress/temperature of the room if you practice and home, and much more. 25MjWaPwVF4.title: 13 Minute Balancing Yoga Practice
25MjWaPwVF4.description:
Here's a balancing sequence you can do from anywhere - you don't even really need a yoga mat! This video is brought to you by Las Catalinas in Costa Rica - a really amazing walkable town close to Liberia, Costa Rica. They have apartments on property as well as a hotel: https://www.santarenahotel.com/. 

For this practice, you don't even need a yoga mat. We'll begin by finding our center point of gravity and then move into various balancing poses including tree pose, warrior three, some twists, and more. As always, move within a pain-free range, take breaks as needed, and remember to breathe deeply. Hope you enjoy!

1UGs2beitI8.title: 15 Minute Yoga in Bed
1UGs2beitI8.description:
This is a gentle, total body yoga stretch video that can be done right from the comfort of your own bed. For this video, I'm in Kansas City at the Raphael Hotel (https://www.raphaelkc.com/) in a gorgeous room that they generously put me up in for our Fall Yoga Workshop Tour. For this video, you will just need some pillows, which we will use as props that will feel great for anyone dealing with tight hips or restriction through the low back. Wea6TqDqycU.title: 19 Minute Total Body Strengthening Yoga Practice
Wea6TqDqycU.description:
This is a 19 Minute Total Body Strengthening Yoga Practice with a full five minute savasana at the end. This video is brought to you by LifeShield, a really great DIY security system for your home or small business (I use it at my new yoga studio!). For this yoga practice, you may want to start with your own warm up, as we jump right into it here. We'll begin in chair pose to begin to activate the hamstrings and glutes, and continue working on them as we move through the practice. Then we'll continue to lengthen and strengthen through the legs and move into the arms with poses like warrior two, half moon, and goddess pose. As always, work within a pain-free range and take breaks as needed.

rK8cm3eMxrk.title: 30 Minute Yoga Foundations Class with Blocks
rK8cm3eMxrk.description:
This is a 30 minute Yoga Foundations Class with Blocks brought to you by https://beanproducts.com/, who generously supplied me with these two great cork yoga blocks. I am a huge fan of cork yoga blocks because they are more stable and firm than foam blocks, and yet have just the right amount of give to them so they're comfortable to sit on or lay over. This is an ideal class for all - from total beginners to seasoned yogis who just want to dial it in to the alignment of their practice. As always, move within a pain-free range, and take breaks as needed. Let me know how it goes for you down in the comments section below!

dGzA7j9HaFE.title: 25 Minute Core Strengthening Yoga Flow with Blocks
dGzA7j9HaFE.description:
This is a 25 minute core strengthening yoga flow video brought to you by 2nd Wind Health and Fitness, which you can find here: https://2ndwindhealth.com/collections/yoga_accessories. There are four parts to the core, and this video addresses all of them - the internal and external obliques, the transverse abdominis and the rectus abdominis. If you're looking to strengthen your core, give this a try. As always, move within a pain-free range and take breaks as needed. A strong core may help with posture, low back pain, and may help prevent injuries. I hope you enjoy! Let me know how it goes for you down in the comments section below!

fuUgc_W6sHE.title: Upper Body Strength Move for Yoga
fuUgc_W6sHE.description:
If you're looking to build more strength to complement your yoga practice, consider adding in this upper back, shoulder and biceps strength move. All you'll need is a pair of light dumbbells or wooden yoga blocks would work as well. Try to 5-8 of these at the top of your vinyasa practice, and keep incorporating them with each vinyasa you do in your flow. The move helps to build upper back, shoulder and biceps strength - all of which will be helpful for your inversion practice, your posture, and in life.

IBhgcSMd7WY.title: 20 Minute Gentle Yoga in Bed Video
IBhgcSMd7WY.description:
If you're looking to cool down and unwind at the end of a long day, or are looking to gently wake your body up at the beginning of the day, this video is something you can do right from the comfort of your own bed! We'll gently work the shoulders, chest, inner thighs, hamstrings, and outer thighs with this twenty minute yoga practice in bed. If you have a bolster, use that, but otherwise, you could just use a couple pillows. As always, move within a pain-free range, and let me know how it goes for you down in the comments section below!

4LdCpmu7qDE.title: Restorative Yoga Practice with Yoga Bolsters
4LdCpmu7qDE.description:
This is a (nearly) 30 minute restorative yoga practice to de-stress, unwind, decrease tension and help calm the nervous system. It's great for yogis of all ages and all levels - particularly those dealing with a lot of stress or anxiety. For this yoga practice, I am using three yoga bolsters which were generously sent to me by HuggerMugger.com. That said, you don't need to have yoga bolsters to do this practice - get creative and use something like a couch cushion or thick rolled blankets. Hope you enjoy!

Kdz0JPmx_xs.title: Core Strengthening Circuit for Ab Strength with FitJoy
Kdz0JPmx_xs.description:
This video is brought to you by FitJoy, the creator of healthy snack alternatives. Check out their FitJoy bars, a grain-free, non gmo, delicious snack: https://fitjoyfoods.com/products/grandmas-lemon-square-fun-size-bar. 

In this video, we are doing a Core Strengthening Circuit aimed at helping to strengthen the core, particularly the lower core. This will help support the lumbar spine, so is definitely something to do if you're experiencing minor back pain. Strengthening the low core is also really beneficial for people working on their inversions, so if you're aiming to deepen your physical asana practice, start incorporating this video into your practice. I would recommend starting off with this video once or twice a week and working up to three or four times per week. Hope you enjoy!

xOhkKb99SAY.title: Five Ways to Use Resistance Bands
xOhkKb99SAY.description:
Today I'm partnering up with ProSource Fit, who generously sent me two long loop resistance bands (http://shrsl.com/1n4qq) which have been really awesome to help with my strength building, and I thought I would share five ways I've been using them here in this video. You can use coupon code YBC20 for 20% off. 

Band Pull-Apart Exercise - This is a great exercise for building the upper back muscles, which is key when you’re getting ready to add inversions like headstand and handstand into your yoga practice. Start with the resistance band out in front of you with arms extended and band pulled taught. Then as you exhale, pull the band apart as far as you comfortably can. Repeat 6-12 times for 3-4 sets. 

Banded Lateral Steps - Great for building glutes and leg strength, banded lateral steps are an easy exercise to incorporate into your yoga practice for added strength building work. Begin by stepping onto the resistance band, positioning it under your arches. Then twist the upper part of the loop once and pull up about halfway. Find a slight hip hinge and bend the knees a bit. Then, laterally step for a few steps and go back in the opposite direction for the other side. Repeat 4 steps on your mat side to side for 3-4 sets. 

Seated Banded Row - Another good exercise for the upper back, the banded row feels really good with a band with more resistance like the 50-120lb one I’m using in the video. Begin with your legs extended and remove the flesh from under your sitting bones. Position the resistance band around the center of your feet and reach down to extend your arms as far as you comfortable can without compromising the position of your legs. As you exhale, use your back strength to pull the band back as you squeeze the upper back. Repeat 6 -12 times for 3-4 sets. 

Banded Loop Squat - These are fantastic for glute strength. Step into the resistance band, positioning the center of your feet over the band. Take your feet about hip distance, with toes slightly pointing out away from you. Squat down and loop the band over your shoulders, bringing your arms through the band and then hold on with your hands. You should feel resistance immediately. As you exhale, press into your feet to activate the glutes and hamstrings and stand up. Go up and down in the squatting position 6-12 times for 3-5 sets. 

Stretching - Use the large loop resistance band the same way you would use a yoga strap. In the video here, I’m using it for leg extension in the supine position for a nice hamstring stretch, but you could truly use it any way you would normally use a yoga strap. It’s particularly helpful as you cool down from your workout.

OHuTl8Fe4x4.description:
This is a gentle stretch video for neck and shoulders which I shot in Kenya. This is a great sequence for all levels, but is very basic. If you're expecting to sweat, this is NOT the video for you. Instead, this will aim to gently wake up the body, with particular attention paid to the neck, shoulders, and upper back. Hope you enjoy. As always, move with intention and always back off of anything that is painful.

bDmIok4V7oI.description:

pyVODOLZ-m8.title: Favorite Things: November
pyVODOLZ-m8.description:
A new episode of Favorite Things, where I share a few new finds I think you might enjoy. 

Jewelry from LYS Jewelry (https://lysjewelry.com/discount/CANDACE20): I’ve been crazy about this necklace ever since LYS sent it to me about a month and a half ago. It smells so beautiful (it’s made out of sandalwood), and is excellent for meditation. The business, owned by a Chinese and French couple, is based on lithotherapy (ancestral technique using gemstones to promote health). Their eco-friendly packaging is also great for travel as you can see in the video! Use code Candace20 for 20% off.

 Skyroam Solis (https://www.skyroam.com?rfsn=1065456.bef50c): I had their older version of this hotspot and fell in love with how easy it was to use, and how reliable it was, even on the African Plains in Kenya! The newer version is sleeker, even more reliable, and also doubles as a power bank for your phone - honestly, everything a traveler who works on the road needs! Use code yogabycandace for a 10% discount.

Buckles’ New Favorite Dog Food (https://www.amazon.com/Only-Natural-Pet-Holistic-Grain-Free/dp/B014LRESLO/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&qid=1541008029&sr=8-1&keywords=max+meat+beef+with+pumpkin&linkCode=sl1&tag=yoga06c-20&linkId=b137340551317e214e6bc731fb7e6ec0&language=en_US): I’d been searching for high quality treats when I stumbled across this grain-free, grass fed dog food. It’s air dried, so it has the consistency of jerky (and smells like jerky, too!), and I’ve been using it as training treats with my ten year old Siberian Husky Buckles, who just loves it. 

Please subscribe to the YouTube channel so you don’t miss out on our weekly yoga classes!

IKbY06g7mn0.title: Travel Vlog: Yoga Workshop Fall Tour Recap
IKbY06g7mn0.description:
In October 2018, YBC® hit the road for a fall yoga workshop tour! We went to DC first (video here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6-AXfni2zd0 ), then Dallas, Chicago, LA, Denver and Vancouver. 

Video notes: 
In Boston I stayed at Hotel Marlowe, a Kimpton hotel. 
In Dallas, we dined at Oddfellows (fantastic coffee).
In Chicago, I stayed at Extended Stay America at Chicago O'Hare airport, and the only redeeming quality was the airport shuttle. Other than that, it was dirty, and the customer service was atrocious.
In LA I stayed at www.TheHollywoodHotel.com, had a facial by www.melissalekus.com, and ate at Tocaya Organica. 
In Denver, we partnered with www.cappellos.com for gluten-free, paleo friendly pizza and cookies to serve at our meet and greet event. 
In Vancouver, we stayed at St Regis Vancouver, and had coffee at Matchstick.
All the venues we used were found by our Marketing Director Lauren (www.instagram.com/its_spoons) on PeerSpace.com


Please subscribe to the YouTube channel so you don’t miss out on our weekly yoga classes!

SXKxudC4oWo.title: Guided Meditation for Stress and Relaxation with Bolsters
SXKxudC4oWo.description:
For this video, we'll be doing a guided meditation in supported savasana with three yoga bolsters. These bolsters were generously donated to us from https://www.sunshineyoga.com/yoga-bolsters/ - they're super high quality. I always recommend picking a rectangular bolster because there are so many different ways to use them. The top of the bolster has a handle so it's easy to carry and they've got a protective, machine washable cover so you can clean it easily. If you don't have three bolsters handy, just get creative at home. Use a couch cushion, blankets, thick towels - whatever works best! 

From here, set up the props as shown and you'll come to lay back to support your back and arms. Then, get cozy and we'll move through this guided meditation that's about ten minutes long or so.

Please subscribe to the YouTube channel so you don’t miss out on our weekly yoga classes!

NnSrr29ediQ.title: Pre-Travel Yoga Class: 13 Minutes
NnSrr29ediQ.description:
I shot this pre-travel yoga video while in Athens (check out the vlog here: https://www.yogabycandace.com/blog/travel-diary-santorini-and-athens). This video meant to help relax your mind and prep your body for a long day of travel. We start with some gentle spinal awakening, and then work our way up to the neck, arms, and then we move to the side body, intending to open up as much as we can. From there, we will do a little hip opening and then you'll be ready to be on your way! Happy Travels! 

Please subscribe to the YouTube channel so you don’t miss out on our weekly yoga classes!

gpvsWAVXJp4.description:

Get creative, use what you have, go grab it, and give this video a try. Yin is a slow practice - you won't be moving a whole lot - you'll be very passive in each pose, and it's great for flexibility.

2bITqdhnXX8.title: Travel Vlog: Muscat, Oman
2bITqdhnXX8.description:
I recently was invited to collaborate with Shangri-La Al Husn Resort and Spa (http://www.shangri-la.com/muscat/alhusnresortandspa/) in Muscat, Oman, so I went with YBC's® Strength and Conditioning Coach Dan Tavino after our Namaslay® Yoga Teacher Training program.

At the international hotel, things are a little more relaxed, so you can wear sleeveless tops, shorts, and pretty much anything else you'd wear at home. But in town, I chose to cover up out of respect for the Islamic culture. In this video, you'll see the Grand Mosque, which was absolutely beautiful, the souk, and the incredible restaurant Bait Al Luban.

EeuanR3aP4U.title: Travel Vlog: Koh Samui, Thailand
EeuanR3aP4U.description:
In early July, I partnered up with Ritz Carlton Koh Samui: http://bit.ly/RitzCarltonKohSamui

I went to Thailand because we did our first Namaslay® Yoga Teacher Training there (the next one takes place in the US: https://www.yogabycandace.com/blog/2018/5/11/200hr-intensive-namaslay-yoga-teacher-training-in-tennessee). So I went a week before the training so I could get acclimated to the time change. Accompanying me on this trip was Dan (instagram.com/dtslifeinpictures), who was our Strength and Conditioning coach for the yoga teacher training program. He also works at YBC® doing media and Mantra Box® coordination.

While at Ritz Carlton Koh Samui, I did a Muay Thai boxing class, got a facial and massage, and we rented a boat which took us out to Mu Ko Ang National Park, which is honestly the most beautiful place I've ever been.

JDXsNpHcntE.title: Barbell Workout: 5 Minute AMRAP
JDXsNpHcntE.description:
5 Minute AMRAP of 3 Power Cleans - 3 Front Squats - 3 Push Press

This video is brought to you by ProSourceFit. They have supplied the flooring, barbell (http://shrsl.com/11jmb), plates (http://shrsl.com/11jme), and clips (http://shrsl.com/11jmd 
). They have all the equipment necessary to start building your home gym. You can use coupon code YBC20 for 20% off!


AMRAP stands for As Many Rounds/Reps as Possible

In this workout we will be performing a barbell complex (suggested weights are 95# for men/55# for women).
 
The 3 movements in the complex are; 
Power Clean
Front Squat
Push Press

The goal is to perform all 9 reps without dropping the barbell. Then, take a few breaths and try to complete another round. You will continue this for 5 minutes. 
If you need to drop the barbell, or break up a round, that is fine. Just pick up where you left off and finish the round. 

Please subscribe to the YouTube channel so you don’t miss out on our weekly yoga classes!

oMWHw6QOVxw.title: Workout Video: 8 Minute Kettlebell Workout
oMWHw6QOVxw.description:
This video is brought to you by ProSourceFit. They have supplied the flooring (http://shrsl.com/115sy) and kettlebells (they offer vinyl covered kettlebells: http://shrsl.com/11jn5 and cast iron kettlebells: http://shrsl.com/11jn6)
*****You can use coupon code YBC20 for 20% off of your order*****

In this workout we will be using a Kettlebell for the 2 movements. The first movement is a Russian KettleBell swing and the second movement is a goblet hold reverse lunge. Find a weight that works for you. 

We will perform 10 reps of each movement, then 9 of each, then 8, and so on until 1 rep of each. 

10 Russian KB swings
10 Goblet Hold Reverse Lunges (10each leg alternating)
9 Russian KB swings
9 Goblet Hold Reverse Lunges (9 each leg alternating)
8 Russian KB swings
8 Goblet Hold Reverse Lunges (8 each leg alternating)
All the way down to 1 Russian KB swing and 1 Goblet Hold Reverse Lunges 

The goal is to keep a consistent pace while maintaining proper form. It is OK to break up a round and take a breath if needed. 

Enjoy

localized.title: Workout Video: 8 Minute Kettlebell Workout
localized.description:
This video is brought to you by ProSourceFit. They have supplied the flooring (http://shrsl.com/115sy) and kettlebells (they offer vinyl covered kettlebells: http://shrsl.com/11jn5 and cast iron kettlebells: http://shrsl.com/11jn6)
*****You can use coupon code YBC20 for 20% off of your order*****

In this workout we will be using a Kettlebell for the 2 movements. The first movement is a Russian KettleBell swing and the second movement is a goblet hold reverse lunge. Find a weight that works for you. 

We will perform 10 reps of each movement, then 9 of each, then 8, and so on until 1 rep of each. 

10 Russian KB swings
10 Goblet Hold Reverse Lunges (10each leg alternating)
9 Russian KB swings
9 Goblet Hold Reverse Lunges (9 each leg alternating)
8 Russian KB swings
8 Goblet Hold Reverse Lunges (8 each leg alternating)
All the way down to 1 Russian KB swing and 1 Goblet Hold Reverse Lunges 

The goal is to keep a consistent pace while maintaining proper form. It is OK to break up a round and take a breath if needed. 

Enjoy

Please subscribe to the YouTube channel so you don’t miss out on our weekly yoga classes!

h60ZvwA8He0.title: Pre or Post Workout Cool Down and Warm Up
h60ZvwA8He0.description:
This fifteen minute full body yoga cool down can be done before or after a workout, run, hike, or really any physical activity. You don't even need a yoga mat to do this. We'll begin by opening up through the side body, the arms, chest, shoulders, and then move into the hamstrings, hip flexors, inner thighs, and torso rotation. As always, work within a pain-free range, listen to your body, and take breaks as needed.

0TXIAlgJLKU.title: 22 Minute Vinyasa Yoga Flow Class
0TXIAlgJLKU.description:
This is a 22 minute vinyasa flow yoga class. Vinyasa means that you are linking breath with movement in an athletic, movement-based yoga class. If you are looking for a slow, stretching style of yoga, this is not the one to do. If you are looking to maybe work up a little bit of a sweat and move mindfully in an athletic way, then vinyasa is the style to do and this video should work perfectly. As always, work within a pain-free range.

AE-hm_SnqrE.title: Yoga for Tight Hips
AE-hm_SnqrE.description:
This 23 minute yoga practice is for my people with tight hips! If you're super super tight, I recommend practicing hip opening at least two to three times per week and you'll start to see improvement within 6-9 weeks for sure. Tight hips can contribute to low back pain, so it's really important to loosen up those tight hips! As always, listen to your body, move within a pain-free range, and take breaks as needed.

MEg1UXR_Nxc.title: Yoga and Pranayama for De-stressing and Anxiety
MEg1UXR_Nxc.description:
This nearly 10 minute practice should do the trick if you're someone who needs a quick way to reconnect to yourself, calm down and re-center yourself. The yoga and breathing video starts with a pranayama exercise (a breathing exercise). I'll guide you through the breathwork which should help slow down your heart rate, calm your mind, and begin to ease stress. From there, we will do a little bit of movement to facilitate better breathing and help open up the lungs. It definitely isn't a long yoga practice with much movement to it, but I created this for people who are super busy and just want a quick way to help ease anxieties and stress. 
 
Please subscribe to the YouTube channel so you don’t miss out on our weekly yoga classes!

9PwwtEoaxbI.title: Quick Yoga For Arm Strength
9PwwtEoaxbI.description:
For this quick arm strength video, you're going to need a heavy book or a yoga block (preferably a cork or wooden yoga block). We'll start with a centering, and then move into a shoulder strengthening exercise, before coming into plank then side plank, and then we'll move into two different types of push ups before doing the whole thing one more time through. As always, be gentle with yourself, listen to your body, work within a pain-free range, and take breaks as needed.

y1tQsy6MFjM.title: Chair Yoga for Tight Hips
y1tQsy6MFjM.description:
In this nearly twenty minute yoga practice, we are incorporating the use of a CHAIR. A chair is a great prop that can be used in the yoga practice a number of different ways. For our purposes, we'll be using it for this hip opening practice. You could even do this on your lunch break at the office (if you have a private office, or if your office is super laid back and no one would think twice about you laying on the floor and stretching). Either way, give it a try and let me know how it goes down in the comments section below. Always move within a pain-free range and take breaks as needed. 

PS: For those wondering, my chair is from here: https://amzn.to/2y1b8ab and the chair cushion is from Ikea.

_FjYrMjGD_A.title: Namaslay® 30 Day Supplemental Glute Strengthening Program
_FjYrMjGD_A.description:
A few months ago, I wrote this post on glute strength: https://www.yogabycandace.com/blog/movements-to-build-glute-strength and we had a number of requests to develop a program for people who are new to strength building, so we did. This 30 Day program is designed by our Strength and Conditioning coach Dan Tavino (@dtslifeinpictures on instagram), and you can find it here: https://www.yogabycandace.com/workout-programs/namaslay-supplemental-30-day-glute-strengthening-and-yoga-program

This is not a complete program; the intention is for these exercises to go alongside what you are currently doing. These movements will help invigorate and target muscle groups that may have been ignored. It is designed so that you can do it anywhere - minimal equipment required.

All exercises will have a link to a demo video; so if you are unsure of how to perform the movement just click the link and watch how it is done

There are Yoga Flows included that are designed specifically for the lower body

All exercises can be done without any weights. Simply perform the movement without the prescribed weight. Feel free to be creative as well; chairs, stools, benches, etc… can all be used in substitute for a box. Any items can be used as weights as well. Be safe and have fun.

Optional Equipment - Any gym will have these available, here are some links if you prefer working out at home

Resistance band

Assorted dumbbells/kettlebells*

524BELy9xqo.title: Weird Health Trends: Cryotherapy
524BELy9xqo.description:
Cryotherapy is the local or general use of low temperatures in medical therapy. You essentially stand in what looks like a stand-up tanning bed, but tanning lights that come on, extreme cold comes out. You step inside, wearing your underwear, socks and slippers, and they'll give you a pair of gloves. Then, the timer comes on (3 minutes, ideally, but you can do less if it's too much for you). 

Among others, the health benefits are said to include: 

improved muscle recovery
pain relief
reduced inflammation
reduced anxiety and depression
improved symptoms of eczema

Watch the video to hear my thoughts!

localized.title: Weird Health Trends: Cryotherapy
localized.description:
Cryotherapy is the local or general use of low temperatures in medical therapy. You essentially stand in what looks like a stand-up tanning bed, but tanning lights that come on, extreme cold comes out. You step inside, wearing your underwear, socks and slippers, and they'll give you a pair of gloves. Then, the timer comes on (3 minutes, ideally, but you can do less if it's too much for you). 

Among others, the health benefits are said to include: 

improved muscle recovery
pain relief
reduced inflammation
reduced anxiety and depression
improved symptoms of eczema

Watch the video to hear my thoughts!

vcnknjInbxk.title: 3 Easy Hairstyles for Yoga Class & How to Revive Yoga Class Hair
vcnknjInbxk.description:
While in Italy for our yoga retreat, Lauren and I took some time to film for our Beauty Files series. In this episode, I'm sharing 3 hairstyles perfect for yoga, and then also showing you how I revive my yoga class hair with the help of a little dry shampoo and a comb.

The Looks

Space Buns: This is a cute look for people with medium length hair. For the look, you'll need a comb and two elastics. 
French Braid with a Bun: This is just a fun twist on a messy bun that keeps the hair off the neck and the bangs out of the eyes, which is ideal for yoga. For the look, you'll need a comb and two elastics. 
Side French Braid with Two Mini Buns: This is a look I did all the time when I had super short hair. For the look, you'll need a comb and three elastics.

CJC4Qn2AAHo.title: At-Home Hip Thrust Demo for Glute Strength
CJC4Qn2AAHo.description:
In yoga, we don't do a whole lot of glute strength movements, so this is one you can begin incorporating if you're looking to build that back body strength. You'll need an ottoman or something of similar height. To begin, position your upper back so it's against the ottoman, and then step your feet about halfway away from your body. Then, press into your heels to extend up through your hips. Aim for 3-5 rounds of 15-25 reps, being sure to squeeze the glutes at the top. Try incorporating this movement a few times per week in order to build strength through the glutes. Hope it helps! 

Please subscribe to the YouTube channel so you don’t miss out on our weekly yoga classes!

aHfMwXJEyWY.title: Yoga for Hip Opening Creative Flow Sequence - 30 Minute
aHfMwXJEyWY.description:
In this video, we are going to jump right into a 30 minute yoga for hip opening creative flow sequence - no mat required! Before we start, do a warm up like this: https://www.yogabycandace.com/blog/2015/11/9/5-minute-warm-up-yoga-to-start-your-day and if you're new to Crow Pose, check out this post: https://www.yogabycandace.com/blog/everything-you-need-to-know-crow-pose. 

This is a vinyasa flow, for the most part, which is a quicker paced yoga, and we will hold poses a little bit here and there. If you're looking for a slower style of yoga, google 'yogabycandace yin' or 'yogabycandace restorative' for more. Hope you enjoy!

JdKxNA6qMfk.title: Yoga For the Office - Standing Series - 11 Minute
JdKxNA6qMfk.description:
This is a standing practice - perfect for anyone at the office or in a space where they don't have a mat. If you're looking to get a quick stretch in, this vid's for you! 

We'll have some forward folds to help open up the hamstrings and release tension in the low back. We also have some standing splits in there, which are nice not only for the hamstrings but also the hip flexors as well. We'll open up through the inner thighs and side body as well. As always, work within a pain-free range.

6uyAiDXzuxo.title: 7 Minute Core Strengthening Workout Video with Sliders
6uyAiDXzuxo.description:
I am using sliders (http://amzn.to/2ouIfMv) for this workout, but if you don't have sliders, get creative and use something at home. Paper plates will work on carpeted surfaces, and washcloths will work on hardwood floors. For this workout we are doing three movements for 20 seconds each and will repeat the whole thing 2 more times for a total of three times through (each round will have a 30 second rest period during which I'll show you some sights from elotrolado.com.pa, where this is filmed, in Panama). The app I am using is called Timer App. Hope you enjoy!

5_EuRZWESLk.title: Core Strength Hiit Workout
5_EuRZWESLk.description:
For this hiit workout we will do repetitions of two movements at 21 - 15 - 9. The two movements are hollow rocks and sit ups, so we will do 21 hollow rocks, 21 sit ups, then 15 hollow rocks and 15 sit ups, and then 9 hollow rocks and 9 sit ups. I offer a few ways to modify the hollow rocks, and for the sit ups, you can slide your feet underneath your couch if you need a bit of anchoring, or you can do the sit ups and just not sit *all* the way up. 

Please subscribe to the YouTube channel so you don’t miss out on our weekly yoga classes!

YMQZ_3MIpQs.title: 5 Minute Guided Meditation to Start the Day
YMQZ_3MIpQs.description:
This is a five minute guided meditation to start your day off on the right foot. I filmed this in Colorado in the Rocky Mountains and was actually struggling with altitude sickness, where I couldn't catch my breath, so that's why the guided meditation teaches you to silently count the length of your inhales and exhales instead of walking you through each breath. Hope you enjoy this guided meditation and intention setting! Please leave your thoughts in the comments section below and don't forget to share with any stressed out friends you have :)

SXINeuZkpFw.title: 30 Minute Restorative Hip Opening Gentle Yoga Practice
SXINeuZkpFw.description:
This is a thirty minute restorative hip opening gentle yoga practice. If you're looking for an athletic practice, this isn't it. Instead, this focuses on opening up tight areas through the hips, which in turn may help to alleviate minor lower back pain. You'll need a yoga strap and a yoga block for this practice. If you don't have a yoga strap, use a belt or a tie. Hope you enjoy!

tKoEr6fP1JE.title: Review: I took a WTRX class at Life Time Fitness with Speedo USA
tKoEr6fP1JE.description: A few weeks ago, I took a WTRX class at Life Time Fitness in partnership with Speedo USA. WTRX is a new water extreme class now available at select Life Time Fitness locations across the US. It will challenge your impression of the traditional aqua class because it combines the camaraderie of the ultimate bootcamp format with lower impact water movements. It was a challenging work out and I loved that it helps to build strength, making it an excellent complement to the yoga practice. Check it out here: http://www.speedousa.com/speedofit-classes #GetSpeedoFit #Ad #Fitness

QHwpFINkhMI.title: Travel Workout: Quick Hiit Workout
QHwpFINkhMI.description:
This hiit workout was filmed in Dubai at Palace Downtown Dubai. This is a quick hiit workout you can do at home or on the road - all you need is a bed. We'll do three exercises, ten reps each, three times through. The first exercise is a step up, the second exercise is a push up, and the last exercise is a Bulgarian split squat. Move at your own pace and take breaks as needed. As always, move within a pain-fre range.

Click here for more pictures and the full run down: http://yogabycandace.com/blog/kenya-safari-yoga-retreat-recap 
In August we hosted a Kenya Safari Yoga Retreat at The Safari Cottages in Ol Pejeta Conservancy. We took twice daily game drives, met Sudan, the last male northern white rhino in the world, and had the most memorable week! Head to yogabycandace.com to join us for upcoming yoga retreats.

Please subscribe to the YouTube channel so you don’t miss out on our weekly yoga classes!

Our book is now available on Amazon: http://amzn.to/2fMPcBj

KOdEdX9Z5co.title: 6 Minute Bodyweight Hiit Workout
KOdEdX9Z5co.description:
Hello from London! I stayed at the Montcalm Royal London House (https://goo.gl/tQ59iv) last month, where they gave me a gorgeous room that opened up onto this astroturf terrace - the perfect location for a bodyweight hiit workout! 
In this hiit workout, we will be doing 3 movements, 10 reps each, one full time through (although you could do is twice through if it's not enough of a workout for you). Remember to warm up first and always move within a pain-free range.
Hope you enjoy! 

Please subscribe to the YouTube channel so you don’t miss out on our weekly yoga classes!

gAIQHrMgHd4.title: 8 Minute Glute Workout with Bands
gAIQHrMgHd4.description:
For this workout, you're going to need bands. I used the x-heavy for thighs and heavy for calves from this kit: http://amzn.to/2sJQrML

This video starts with me demonstrating how to do a glute bridge, banded walks, and banded air squats. Then, we start the workout, doing 10 reps of each movement for three rounds. My glutes were BURNING (especially during the banded walks!). Take breaks as needed, and enjoy! 


Please subscribe to the YouTube channel so you don’t miss out on our weekly yoga classes!

wfzZOsZBd3s.title: 20 Minute Beginner Vinyasa Yoga Video
wfzZOsZBd3s.description:
This video is brought to you by Kimpton The Gray in Chicago which you can check out here: http://www.grayhotelchicago.com/

This is a twenty minute vinyasa yoga video that's a great option for beginners, as it is a moderately paced vinyasa class. Vinyasa means MOVEMENT, so there will be little to no static holds. If you're looking for a good stretch, google 'yogabycandace restorative' or 'yogabycandace yin yoga'. If you're looking to break into a moderately paced vinyasa class as a relatively new beginner, then this will be your jam. 

Hope you enjoy. 

Please subscribe to the YouTube channel so you don’t miss out on our weekly yoga classes!

h-LS2SgrqFU.title: Core Workout: Hollow Rock Holds
h-LS2SgrqFU.description:
Here's a great quick core workout you can do to help build a strong core foundation through your abdominals. We'll hold a hollow rock hold position - everything tight through the midline - for twenty seconds. Then we'll rest for ten seconds, and then repeat that three more times through for a total of four times. Hope you enjoy!
Please subscribe to the YouTube channel so you don’t miss out on our weekly yoga classes!

Vtn2pbopVh8.title: 10 Minute Lunch Break Short Vinyasa Yoga Flow
Vtn2pbopVh8.description:
Need a quick pick-me-up? This should do! 

This short yoga flow is vinyasa style, which means you link breath with movement for a more athletic style of flow. You will not be holding yoga poses for an extended period of time (search 'restorative yoga' if that's the kind of yoga you're looking for). This is a quicker pace, and it's meant to be quicker. As always, move within a pain-free range and always honor your abilities. 

Please subscribe to the YouTube channel so you don’t miss out on our weekly yoga classes!

CmRuNdzvim4.title: 9 Minute Hiit Workout - Rowing, V-ups and Back Lunges
CmRuNdzvim4.description:
This hiit workout video was made in partnership with Kimpton Marlowe Hotel http://www.hotelmarlowe.com/. Be sure to check out our other hiit workout videos filmed at their gym and our 60 minute yoga video filmed in room!

Here's another Hiit workout you can do on the road or at the gym if you have access to a rower. But if you don't have a rower, no worries - you can still do this. Instead of the rowing, do jumping jacks or run. 

We will do 3 rounds: a 200m row (or if you're not rowing, you'll do jumping jacks or run 200m which is about 2 blocks), then we'll do 12 v-ups, and then 10 back lunges... and repeat that whole thing two more times through for a total of 3 rounds.

Please subscribe to the YouTube channel so you don’t miss out on our weekly yoga classes!

2t1bF7lqEHs.title: Hiit Workout: Dumbbell Snatch and Air Squats
2t1bF7lqEHs.description:
For this hiit workout we'll be combining dumbbell snatches with air squats in a 21-15-9-15-21 count. So it'll go: 21 dumbbell snatches, 21 air squats, then 15 dumbbell snatches, 15 air squats, 9 dumbbell snatches, 9 air squats, and back up to 21. It's tough but take breaks as needed, or modify and just do the first part (21-15-9). 

Use whatever weight feels comfortable to you (I believe I am using 20lb weight). 

This video was filmed at Hotel Marlowe, a Kimpton hotel in Cambridge, Mass.

ofJhsMrpuwA.title: 6 Minute Plank Video for Core Strength
ofJhsMrpuwA.description:
Here's a somewhat torturous planking video to help build core strength. We'll do a forearm plank for 1 minute, side plank on the right for one minute, side plank on the left for 1 minute, and then repeat one more time through. It's tough but if I can do it, you can do it! Take breaks as needed and always work within a pain-free range.

My pants are from Yoga Design Lab and the bralette and top are from Free People.

bcjRmVfFZjA.title: 6 Minute Hiit Workout
bcjRmVfFZjA.description:
This hiit workout is brought to you by Clever Yoga, who sent us their balance pad, which has a number of great uses. Check it out here: http://amzn.to/2mdcRm6

This hiit workout is fast yet effective for increasing your heart rate and burning fat. 
We'll do 5 rounds of 3 movements. The movements are handstand push ups, air squats and mountain climbers. If you cannot do handstand pushups, you could do a handstand hold against the wall or a regular push up on the floor. We will do 3 handstand push ups (or 3 second handstand hold or 3 regular push ups), 6 air squats, and 9 mountain climbers. 
Please subscribe to the YouTube channel so you don’t miss out on our weekly yoga classes!

zDxJlYVzOV8.title: Under 10 Minutes: Hiit Workout
zDxJlYVzOV8.description:
In this hiit workout, we will do 20 double unders with a jumprope (or just do jumping jacks if you don't have a jumprope), followed by 20 Russian twists (option to make it more challenging by adding a yoga block or weighted med ball), and 20 in and out jumping squats. As always, move within a pain-free range, listen to your body, and take rests as needed.

If you need a bit more help learning each of these movements - opt-in to our Exclusive Section on our App, which is available here for iOS: https://goo.gl/19QE0f and here for Google Play: https://goo.gl/crfZ5E.

eZhe6gUaJYo.title: How to Jump Back from Crow Pose
eZhe6gUaJYo.description:
This ten minute video will be helpful for my intermediate people are just starting to learn to jump back from crow pose. This requires good opening through your hips, and a good amount of upper body and core strength, so if you don't get it right off the bat, try not to get discouraged. Instead, keep practicing and you will see improvement.

6IaGZcFArZU.title: 4 Minute Guided Mantra Meditation for Confidence
6IaGZcFArZU.description:
In this four minute guided mantra meditation for confidence, we'll begin with a few centering breaths just to clear the mind. Then, we'll begin breathing in and out through the nose and begin the mantra. As you inhale, think "confidence" and visualize yourself feeling more and more confident, and as you exhale, think "doubt" and visualize that doubt leave your body. I recommend doing this any time you feel sort of down, low, or filled with hesitation or self-doubt. Remember that you are stronger than you know and more powerful than you realize.

HHRV3Kk4M80.title: 20 Minute Back Body Strength Yoga Video
HHRV3Kk4M80.description:
This is a twenty minute yoga video to develop back body strength through the posterior chain - the glutes, hamstrings, back, and more. We'll begin with a centering to find calmness and stillness. From here we'll move into child's pose and from there move into sphinx pose, some push ups, and then move into a flow that includes downward facing dog, lunges, warrior three, and more. We'll explore utkatasana (chair pose) to fire up the legs, and squats. Then, we will do a bit of back body strengthening while on our stomachs. I hope you enjoy!

tr5TAwzAFpA.title: 10 Minute Yoga in Bed for Neck, Shoulders and Arms
tr5TAwzAFpA.description:
This ten minute yoga video focuses on the neck, shoulders and arms to help relieve tightness and tension. This can be done right from bed, either first thing in the morning or right before you go to sleep. Or, it can be a warm up before yoga or the gym and can be done on a yoga mat. As always, listen to your body and honor how you feel. We'll begin seated and do a short centering. Then, we'll do some side body opening, gentle stretching for the neck and shoulder area and then stretch the arms. You should finish the video feeling de-stressed and loose. Hope you enjoy!

lOjotp4JENE.title: 3 Minute Upper Body Hiit Workout
lOjotp4JENE.description:
Thanks for tuning into today's hiit workout video! This video is brought to you by Mother Dirt. Mother Dirt created the first and only live probiotic for the skin. This is an amazing breakthrough for people who sweat a lot because it contains a healthy bacteria that literally consumes the ammonia in your sweat, which is the stinky and irritating part. Using their AO+ Mist before or after you workout helps reduce body odor and makes your skin feel smooth and refreshed. They also have 2 supporting products - the Shampoo and Cleanser. All Mother Dirt products have 10 ingredients or less, are plant-based, sulfate-free, preservative free, fragrance free, eco-friendly, and biome-friendly! We have a special treat for Yoga by Candace fans - get 25% off your order on Motherdirt.com with promo code  Yogabycandace25 by clicking this link: http://shop.motherdirt.com/shop/?ref=yoga-b-c_video

In today's hiit workout, we are going to do a fast yet effective series of movements. It's challenging especially for the upper body and shoulder area. Always listen to your body, honor how you feel, and work within a pain-free range. 

The first movement is a shoulder tap. Come into a plank position and rock side to side as you touch your hand to your shoulder. We will do this ten times.

The next movement is mountain climbers, where you will quickly change feet ten times.

The last movement is a push up. You can modify this by coming down onto your knees. Just make sure your hips are forward so your body is in a diagonal line. I like to have my elbows straight back behind me just like in chaturanga. We will do five push ups during each round.

We'll go through each series of movements three times. 

Please subscribe to the YouTube channel so you don’t miss out on our weekly yoga classes!

Ooy4yIFAnjU.title: 15 Minute Slow Flow Yoga
Ooy4yIFAnjU.description:
This week's slow flow yoga practice is great to warm up first thing in the morning, cool down after a workout or run, or wind down at the end of the day. We will start with a centering to ground yourself, and work on the ujjayi breath. Then we'll come into child's pose, and do some variations to open up the side body. Slowly from there we will begin the flow. Vinyasa means flow so we will be constantly moving in a slow flow manner. Cobra pose comes next, then child's, then we will round forward and come into downward facing down. We'll open up the hip flexors and hamstrings, and move through a playfully sequenced flow. I hope you love it! 

Please subscribe to the YouTube channel so you don’t miss out on our weekly yoga classes!

8oaHrVYzIVs.title: 5 Minute Bodywieght Hiit Workout
8oaHrVYzIVs.description:
Don't let the short time fool you - this hiit workout is no joke. You just need your body for this - no equipment needed! 

We're doing three rounds of three movements - ten reps each. We'll start with jumping lunges. Then, we'll move directly into jumping squats - take your feet a little wider than your hips, toes pointed slightly out away from you, and lead with your butt as you squat down and explode up in a jump. Lastly, the third movement will be hollow rocks. Bring your arms in line with your ears, legs raised and extended, and you'll rock using your core strength.

0wGSVns3Xy8.title: Ask A Trainer Series: How To Do Jerks
0wGSVns3Xy8.description:
This is the second post in our mini series Ask a Trainer where James Keeler, trainer and co-owner of Focused Movement Academy gives a thorough explanation of different variations of jerks. Before you watch this, make sure you've watched the video on how to do cleans: http://yogabycandace.com/blog/how-to-do-cleans.

Here's a quick break down of the video: 
1:00 how to do push press
1:09 tip: keep your elbows up so the bar stays on your shoulders. if your shoulders drop, the bar will come down onto your clavicle. 
1:15 tip: keep your knees out
1:33 keep hips under you for good alignment 


2:26 how to do push jerk
2:44 tip: jump and push, lock arms and land
3:19 what not to do: dip too far 
3:27 instead: do a quick dip for bar flexion
3:36 what not to do: lead with your hips. doing this will send the bar forward
3:41 instead: keep your weight in your heels, knees out and hips stacked under you


3:49 how to do split jerks
4:08 tip: picture a box. your front foot lands on the front corner, and your back foot will land on the opposite back corner
4:33 tip: end where you started. step front first first, then back foot.
4:52 what not to do: dip too fast
5:07 instead: do a controlled dip
5:18 what not to do: land too tall (this means you're pressing the bar up rather than using your hips)
5:36 instead: land low. treat low weight like it's heavy so you develop proper technique from the start
5:54 what not to do: land with your feet too close
6:27 instead: land with wide feet for more stability
6:54 tip: be sure to tuck your chin
7:19 tip: dip, pause, drop to help get under the bar
7:55 how to figure out which foot goes first

abTdkGCeurg.title: Ask A Trainer Series - How to do Cleans - Olympic Lifts
abTdkGCeurg.description:
Over on the blog (yogabycandace.com), we'd had a lot of people ask about Olympic lifts. I enlisted the help of my friend, trainer and nutrition coach James Keeler from Focused Movement Academy in Miami to help out. Read more at yogabycandace.com/how-to-do-cleans.


2:14 - what not to do: pull too early, when the bar is at your knees. instead, wait until you're at full extension with your hips

3:12 - what not to do: reverse curl. instead, elbows out in front, catch the weight in your shoulders


3:58: how to do a muscle clean

4:21: start from the hang (just above the knee)

4:38: tip: high elbows

5:11: how to do: hang power clean 

5:24: Power clean is the same as muscle clean, but re-dip the knees

5:38 Tip: Violent hip extension, then drop drown

6:22: How to do hang squat clean

6:47: What not to do: reverse curl, kettle bell swing the bar (aka "Frankenstein arms")

7:09: What not to do: Lean forward as you pull from the pocket. Instead: stand tall first, then pull.

8:11: Full clean

8:29: Tip: load the hamstrings to lift the bar

9:13: Tip: push the knees back until you're at the hang position

PWlQ7Hf5DLk.description:
Today's yoga video is a 20 minute yoga sequence for core strength. This is the video you'll want to do to help build strength for poses like handstand, and other inversions. Building solid abdominal strength is also excellent for helping to prevent back pain, so I always recommend core strengthening for people dealing with back issues. As always, move with intention and avoid pain. Take rests as needed and always listen to you body.

Os-ZtcHiRTE.title: Namaslay - Yogabycandace Book Now Available on Amazon!
Os-ZtcHiRTE.description:
Introducing Namaslay, now available on Amazon: http://amzn.to/1XsHoEJ 

Namaslay features over 100 yoga poses and offers a distinct visual format that guides the reader through each pose with a series of progressions that are broken down by skill and experience level with step-by-step instructions and full-color photos with tips on overcoming common mistakes to get the most out of every pose.

Namaslay also features three 30-day yoga programs that focus on: de-stress, core strengthening, and back pain.  You will also find specific yoga sequences that are customized for everyone from the office dweller to the endurance athlete. 

Written with heart, humor, and swagger, Namaslay is a book for everyone, whether you’re new to yoga, an advanced practitioner, or even simply curious.

Namaslay’s high-quality, edgy yet beautiful photographs add an artful flair that puts it in a class of its own—as appropriate for a coffee table as the yoga studio!

TXjzgoSI4sg.title: 12 Minute Chair Yoga for Travel and the Office
TXjzgoSI4sg.description:
Here is a relaxing, rejuvenating twelve minute chair yoga sequence that you can do if you're traveling or if you're stuck at the office. This works to release hip tension, low back pain, upper back pain, and helps to open the chest, side body, armpits, and neck. We start with a pranayama exercise to gently awaken the neck and get the lungs working to their fullest capacity, and then we move into gentle stretches. I hope you enjoy!

kw4hwGgxt5Y.description:

d89ISpcJh7M.title: Push Up Party 1-10-1
d89ISpcJh7M.description:
In this week's yoga video, we are working on building upper body strength with pyramid push ups. This means I'll start and do one push up, and then I'll rest while you do one push up. Then, I'll do two push ups while you rest, and will rest while you do two push ups, etc. We'll go up to ten and then back down to one. It's a lot of push ups! Go onto your knees if you need a break, or press pause and catch your breath. Enjoy!

zfuvi76XBfY.title: YBC Favorite Things - Episode 8
zfuvi76XBfY.description:
1. Collagen Peptides - Vital Proteins sent these peptides to me and I've been using these daily in my recovery drinks. (You can use them in hot or cold drinks!) I love that they taste like nothing yet give you a ton of benefits (elasticity in the skin, hair, and stronger nails). Whenever I find something that helps me stay healthy - especially something I can take on the road with me - I am sold. 

2. New kicks - These APL sneakers were sent my way and I have fallen in love. They're extremely lightweight yet still durable, they're breathable, and I like the little hook at the heel which makes slipping them on and off easy.

3. Weekender - This brightly colored bag is a welcomed change from the all black errthang I have going on in my luggage closet. Evolve Fitwear sent it to me and I think it's fantastic even for daily use as a gym or yoga bag because it'll hold everything you need and then some. I also like that you've got the top handles and then the longer shoulder strap so if you're someone who needs to switch it up as you walk to and from your terminal, you have some options. :)

I'd love to know what new finds you've discovered this past month. Anything I should know about? Let me know down in the comments below!

nsJtHBllFuY.description:
Sharing three picks for this month's episode of Favorite Things: 
1. HiQ Face Serum This serum is backed by science. Each ingredient has a purpose in the formula and the end result is a hydrating yet lightweight serum that nourishes the skin. Use code: CANDACEYOGA for 15 % off your entire order. Expires: December 12, 2015. http://www.hiqcosmetics.com/facial-serum-1/

2. Mala Kamala Mala necklace. This handmade necklace comes from Australia, and I love it for a thousand and one reasons. The first being that it comes with information about how to use the mala necklace, how to care for it, and the reasoning behind each type of bead on the necklace. It's just nice when you're new to malas, you know? Use code YBC for 10% off now through Dec 12, 2015. http://malakamala.com/collections/mala-beads/products/amethyst-dream

3. Aura Cacia Revive body cloths. This is a company I have loved for years. I trust them because every single product they put out has pure, good ingredients. Nothing weird or synthetic. Further, they impressed me because while they are a bigger company than I normally support, every single representative I've ever chatted with (I met them at ExpoEast) was kind, knowledgeable, and passionate about their products. That rarely happens when a company gets bigger, you know?  http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B011LNUMLG/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=390957&creativeASIN=B011LNUMLG&linkCode=as2&tag=yoga06c-20&linkId=VDEF6KSFSAHXATUF

qy_oIKf1ByM.title: 30 Minute Power Yoga Class
qy_oIKf1ByM.description:
This is a thirty minute power yoga class. There are options for modifications throughout, so it's okay for people new to yoga (though I wouldn't say it's appropriate for absolute beginners). This is a vinyasa yoga class. Vinyasa means 'movemen't, so we will be constantly flowing and moving through the practice. If you're looking for a slower style with long holds I would recommend a hatha yoga practice. As always, honor your body, and work within a pain-free range.

Please subscribe to the YouTube channel so you don’t miss out on our weekly yoga classes!

B9UKAfRSpEM.description:

_DGkw2Yw6jA.title: Push Up Party 1-5-1
_DGkw2Yw6jA.description:
If you're working on arm balances in yoga, building upper body strength is a great way to help your practice and reach your goals. Here we move through a push-up pyramid workout. You'll want to be sure you're warmed up before you start, and remember that you can always go down to your knees if you're feeling like it's too much. Try to keep your elbows straight back behind you, don't let your shoulders round, and be sure to push out of the bottoms of the feet so the legs are long and strong and the quads are engaged. Hope you enjoy! 

Please subscribe to the YouTube channel so you don’t miss out on our weekly yoga classes!
